{"search_data": "Central Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana Minimum Deposit / Balance Reduced to Rs. 250 Per YearSukanya Samriddhi Yojana Minimum Deposit Per Year & Minimum BalanceTill November 2017, govt. has opened more than 1.26 crore SSY accounts in the name of girl children. These opened Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana Accounts secures an amount of Rs 19,183 crore. SSY Interest Rate is revised on a quarterly basis like other Post Office Savings Schemes. From July to September quarter, the interest rate is fixed at 8.1 per cent. The important features and highlights of this SSY Scheme can be checked using the link below:- Complete Details of PM Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana AccountPeople can now open Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana Account with Minimum Balance of Rs. 250. The maintaining balance and the minimum deposit per year is also reduced from Rs. 1000 to Rs. 250 with maximum limit of Rs. 1,50,000 in a financial year. People can make subsequent deposits in multiples of Rs. 100. People can make deposits in lump-sum and also there is no limit on the number of times in which payment can be made.Any Legal / Natural Guardian can open SSY account in the name of a girl child by producing only the Birth Certificate. There must be only one account for a single girl child upto maximum 2 different accounts for 2 daughters in a single family. For more details, visit the official website:- https://www.indiapost.gov.in/Financial/Pages/Content/Post-Office-Saving-Schemes.aspxThis account attains maturity when the girl child completes 21 years of age after which the money will be given to the bank account of the girl in whose name the account was opened. All the deposits also attracts Tax Benefits and are fully exempted under section 80C of the Income Tax (IT) Act.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}